The paper deals with creating a framework that can automatically create behaviors for game agents of different difficulty classes and enough diversity, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as behavior trees and genetic algorithms (GA). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.GA are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for automated tests, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the use of GA involves optimization, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with managing difficulty levels, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
